Shire Plc (SHP)  said its LDX treatment for
attention deficity hyperactivity disorder was shown to be
effective in a late-stage European study.  The result for the main goal of the study of 336 children
ages 6 to 17 was statistically significant, the Dublin-based
drugmaker said today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
